YENAGOA – The Minister of State for Petroleum Resources, Timipre Sylva, has called on Ijaw youths to emulate the qualities of the Head of Reintegration at the Presidential Amnesty Programme (PAP), Alfred Kemepado. This was contained in a statement on Tuesday by the minister’s Special Assistant, Media and Publicity, Julius Bokoru, to celebrate Kemepado’s 41st birthday. The statement quoted Sylva as saying the Ijaw youth leader had set a standard for youths in the Niger Delta. Ekiti Governorship Election: Kolawole Receives Certificate Of… Bye-Election: Alade Olanrewaju Lawson Wins APC Primary It said, “Sylva believes Alfred Kemepado has distinguished himself and set a standard for youths in the Niger Delta region and Nigeria with his work ethics, vibrancy and innovation.” The minister wished Kemepado “more grace, vigour and purpose to continue and live up to the spectacular trajectory before him.” Kemepado was a former secretary-general of the Ijaw Youth Council (IYC), a former Special Adviser to the Governor of Bayelsa State and until his present position, the special adviser on special duties to the Interim Administrator of PAP, Col. Milland Dikio (rtd).